mechanoreception.notes: As soft corals, Primnoidae likely possess mechanoreceptors to detect water currents and pressure changes, crucial for filter feeding and orientation.

chemoreception.notes: Chemoreception is likely present to detect dissolved organic matter and other chemical cues related to feeding.

photoreception.notes: The presence and functionality of photoreceptors are unknown in this family. While some corals have photosensitive cells, their role in Primnoidae needs further investigation.
